<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17560603-31">
               <interp inst="t17560603-31" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17560603-31" type="year" value="1756"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17560603-31" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17560603"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17560603-31" type="date" value="17560603"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17560603-31-off145-c314" targOrder="Y" targets="t17560603-31-defend369 t17560603-31-off145 t17560603-31-verdict146"></join>
         
               <p>273. (L.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17560603-31-defend369" type="defendantName">
                     Samuel 
                     Arrowsmith 
                  <interp inst="t17560603-31-defend369" type="surname" value="Arrowsmith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17560603-31-defend369" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17560603-31-defend369" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17560603-31-off145" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17560603-31-off145" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17560603-31-off145" type="offenceSubcategory" value="forgery"></interp>
               forging a bill of exchange, drawn upon 
                     
                        <persName id="t17560603-31-victim371" type="victimName">
                           Henry 
                           Clark 
                        <interp inst="t17560603-31-victim371" type="surname" value="Clark"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17560603-31-victim371" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17560603-31-victim371" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17560603-31-off145 t17560603-31-victim371"></join>
                     </persName>
                      
                  
               
                  </rs>, to this purport,</p>
               <p>' Sir, Three months after date pay to Mr. Samuel ' Arrowsmith, or order, one hundred pounds ' for value received, as by advice.</p>
               <p>Your humble servant, T. Griffice.</p>
               <p>' Dec. 23, 1754.</p>
               <p>100 00</p>
               <p>' To Mr. 
               <persName id="t17560603-31-person372">
                  Henry 
                  Clark 
               <interp inst="t17560603-31-person372" type="surname" value="Clark"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17560603-31-person372" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17560603-31-person372" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , Post-master. Bread Street, ' London. - 
               <persName id="t17560603-31-person373">
                  Thomas 
                  Harris 
               <interp inst="t17560603-31-person373" type="surname" value="Harris"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17560603-31-person373" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17560603-31-person373" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , 
               <persName id="t17560603-31-person374">
                  George 
                  Miller 
               <interp inst="t17560603-31-person374" type="surname" value="Miller"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17560603-31-person374" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17560603-31-person374" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , indorsed ' on the back of it'.</p>
               <p>And for publishing the same, well knowing it to have been forged, with intention to defraud.</p>
               <p>The evidence appearing deficient to prove the publication in London, he was <rs id="t17560603-31-verdict146" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17560603-31-verdict146" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               acquitted
            </rs>, and detained to be sent down to the city of Gloucester to take his trial for the same.</p>
            </div1>
